ivardefs.name: bodySite
ivardefs.desc: The anatomic structures examined. See DICOM Part 16 Annex L (http://dicom.nema.org/medical/dicom/current/output/chtml/part16/chapter_L.html) for DICOM to SNOMED-CT mappings. The bodySite may indicate the laterality of body part imaged; if so, it shall be

ivardefs.name: endpoint_
ivardefs.desc: The network service providing access (e.g., query, view, or retrieval) for this series. See implementation notes for information about using DICOM endpoints. A series-level endpoint, if present, has precedence over a study-level endpoint with the same End

ivardefs.name: instance_
ivardefs.desc: A single SOP instance within the series, e.g. an image, or presentation state.

ivardefs.name: laterality
ivardefs.desc: The laterality of the (possibly paired) anatomic structures examined. E.g., the left knee, both lungs, or unpaired abdomen. If present, shall be consistent with any laterality information indicated in ImagingStudy.series.bodySite.

ivardefs.name: modality
ivardefs.desc: The distinct modality for this series. This may include both aquisition and non-aquisition modalities.

ivardefs.name: number
ivardefs.desc: The numeric identifier of this series in the study.

ivardefs.name: numberOfInstances
ivardefs.desc: Number of SOP Instances in the Study. The value given may be larger than the number of instance elements this resource contains due to resource availability, security, or other factors. This element should be present if any instance elements are present.

ivardefs.name: performer_
ivardefs.desc: Indicates who or what performed the series and how they were involved.

ivardefs.name: specimen_
ivardefs.desc: The specimen imaged, e.g., for whole slide imaging of a biopsy.

ivardefs.name: started
ivardefs.desc: The date and time the series was started.

ivardefs.name: uid
ivardefs.desc: The DICOM Series Instance UID for the series.

properties.desc: Each study has one or more series of images or other content.
